## When to use
When you need to quickly assess the status of network interfaces in your system without opening additional tools or windows.

## Approach
Create a custom shell function that utilizes `shell_exec` to run commands like `ip addr show` and display the output. This allows for an immediate view of all active network interfaces and their statuses directly from the terminal.
## Example
```bash
# Add this function definition in your profile script (e.g., ~/.bashrc)
net_status() {
  shell_exec "ip addr show"
}
```
After adding the above line, source your profile script or restart your terminal session to use the `net_status` command. When you run `net_status`, it will display the status of all network interfaces.
## Pitfalls
Ensure that the `shell_exec` tool is available in your environment and properly configured. Also, be aware that the output might be extensive if there are many active interfaces or configurations.